-- Acciona Awarded Clean Energy Contract From Madrid Water Manager
-- B y   R a n d a l l   H a c k l e y
-- 2012-12-11T16:45:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-11/acciona-awarded-clean-energy-contract-from-madrid-water-manager.html
Acciona SA (ANA) , a renewable energy and
water provider, said a subsidiary won a 56 million-euro ($73
million) contract to supply electricity starting next month to
Canal Isabel II Gestion, the Madrid region’s water manager.  Acciona’s green energy developments unit was awarded the
contract to supply energy to facilities of the publicly owned
utility, which operates 14 reservoirs, 13 drinking water
treatment plants and 125 wastewater treatment plants as well as
sewage pipe and water networks across the Madrid area.  Acciona is based in Alcobendas,  Spain .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Randall Hackley in London at 
